properties.headline: Red Flag Warning issued January 21 at 1:40PM EST until January 21 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
...RED FLAG WARNING IN EFFECT FOR LOW HUMIDITY...HIGH ERC VALUES
AND WIND...

.High pressure to the north is filtering in some cool and dry air
over the Florida peninsula today and warranted the issuance of a
red flag warning for this afternoon.

The National Weather Service in Tampa Bay Area - Ruskin FL has
issued a Red Flag Warning, which is in effect until 7 PM EST this
evening.

* AFFECTED AREA...Polk...Coastal Hernando...Coastal
Hillsborough...Inland Hernando...Inland Hillsborough.

* WIND...North around 15 knots with higher gusts.

* HUMIDITY...30 to 35 percent.

* ERC...27-30.

* IMPACTS...any fires that develop will likely spread rapidly.
Outdoor burning is not recommended.
properties.instruction:
A Red Flag Warning means that critical fire weather conditions
are either occurring now....or will shortly. A combination of
strong winds...low relative humidity...and warm temperatures can
contribute to extreme fire behavior.
